@startuml UC-07_Export_Report

title UC-07: Export Usage Report

skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #F1F8E9
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #33691E
skinparam ActivityFontColor #1B5E20
skinparam ArrowColor #33691E

start
:User on Analytics page clicks "Export Report";
:System displays export options modal:\n- Format: PDF, CSV, JSON, Excel\n- Period: Last 7d, 30d, 90d, custom\n- Content sections: Key Metrics, Workflow Performance, Execution Trends, Error Analysis, Integration Usage, Resource Usage\n- Delivery: Download, Email, or Both;

:User confirms export settings;
:System shows "Generating report...";

:AnalyticsService.generate_report() executed:\n- Query all relevant analytics data\n- Aggregate metrics for period\n- Calculate trends and comparisons\n- Build report data structure;

:Format conversion based on selected format:\n- PDF: PDFGenerator creates template with charts, tables, branding\n- CSV: Create CSV rows from metrics with headers\n- JSON: Serialize report object to JSON with metadata\n- EXCEL: Create workbook with multiple sheets (Summary, Workflows, Trends, Errors, Integrations);

:File generation completes;
if (Email selected?) then (Yes)
    :Create email with report attached;
    :EmailService sends to user email;
    :Show "Report sent to {email}";
else (No)
    :Store file in Firebase Storage (temporary);
    :Generate download URL (expires in 7 days);
    :Start browser download;
endif

:Update user usage.exportsThisMonth += 1;
:Analytics logs "report_exported" event;
:Display success notification;
:Report export complete;
stop

@enduml
